com.dukes.lang.parser

Interface Parser

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractTableParser, KleinParser

    public interface Parser

    An interface that describes the workings of a language parser. A parser should be able to identify if a program is valid, and be able to generate an abstract syntax tree. This is done by the isValid() and generateAST() methods, respectively. Note that a parser should be fed a specific scanner in order to make sense of tokens, not characters.

    Since:
    0.2.0

        Generates an abstract syntax tree based on the program.
        Returns:
        An AbstractSyntaxNode that represents the given program.
        Throws:
